"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99815","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-23","<p>The culls were closely monitored and the processes for data collection were independently audited. The results now need to be quality assured and assessed. It would not be appropriate to comment until these steps have been completed.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-10-23T12:13:59.1062168Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99815/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99815/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99815/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-10-20","Bovine Tuberculosis: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the pilot badger culls in (a) Gloucestershire and (b) Somerset have been evaluated as being safe, humane and effective.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","211130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99816","Department for Transport","false","2014-10-23","<p>The National Contingency Plan exercise in Conwy Morfa on 10 and 11 September 2014 was coordinated by the Maritime and Coastguard Agency (MCA) and involved 39 organisations and 180 participants.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The MCA, along with a number of other organisations, will assess how the exercise tested the response to an oil spill incident of national significance.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A formal report on the exercise, detailing lessons identified and recommendations, will be published within the first quarter of 2015. This timescale is necessary because of the complexity and scale of the exercise.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-10-23T11:28:16.9161113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99816/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99816/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99816/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-10-20","Emergencies: Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the recent National Contingency Plan exercise in Conwy Morfa.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","211120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99817","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-23","<p>Water company representatives are currently working with the building industry to produce a code of practice on how they handle requests about extensions to houses situated on land which may contain a sewer. A code should introduce greater transparency about the processes involved, and associated costs.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson","211025","2014-10-23T13:52:40.530528Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99817/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99817/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99817/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-10-20","Housing Improvement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to work with water companies to produce a set of procedures for those involved in the process of extending their properties.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","211100"
